# SPA fallback for client-side routing.
#
# Why this exists
# ---------------
# When a user hits a deep URL (e.g. /event-guidelines, /vn/host-guide) we want
# the host to serve the pre-rendered HTML for that route if it exists, and
# otherwise fall through to index.html so React Router can handle it.
#
# Both Netlify and Cloudflare Pages honor a `_redirects` file. Pre-rendered
# routes ship real HTML at /event-guidelines/index.html, /vn/index.html, etc.,
# so those are served directly — this catch-all only kicks in for routes the
# crawler-facing prerender didn't cover (mostly fat-finger URLs).
#
# Note: netlify.toml has the same catch-all rewrite defined. That one keeps
# Netlify happy; this file keeps Cloudflare Pages happy. They do not conflict.

/*    /index.html   200
